<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<h2>The Program</h2>
<p>The Department offers a minor program in Statistics that consists of five upper division level courses focusing on the fundamentals of mathematical statistics and of the most widely used applied statistical methods.</p>
<h3>Minor Advisors</h3>
<p>For a current list of faculty and staff advisors, see <a href="https://statistics.ucdavis.edu/undergrad/advising" target="_blank">Undergraduate Advising</a>. Students are encouraged to meet with an advisor to plan for the minor as early as possible. </p>
]]>
</informationtext>
